# Contributing to PI Creation Tool

Thank you for considering contributing to PI Creation Tool! 
This multi-platform app offers tools for file management, AI assistance, dashboards, 
quick app generation, etc. All tools are in one HUB, that works as encapsulation of management algorithm, made by Nikita Beregovykh (Liber Creative LLC) for Android, iOS, Windows, and macOS. 
Created by Nikita Beregovykh (Liber Creative LLC), PI Creation Tool is licensed under the BSD 3-Clause License.

## How to Contribute

### Reporting Issues
If you encounter any bugs, have suggestions for improvements, or want to request new features, please open an issue on our GitHub repository. When reporting an issue, please include:

- A clear and descriptive title.
- A detailed description of the problem or suggestion.
- Steps to reproduce the issue (if applicable).
- Any relevant screenshots or logs.

### Submitting Pull Requests
We welcome contributions from the community! To submit a pull request, follow these steps:

1. **Fork the Repository**: Create a personal fork of the repository on GitHub by clicking the "Fork" button at the top right of the repository page.

2. **Clone the Fork**: Clone your fork to your local machine using the following command:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/pi-creation-tool.git

Create a Branch: Create a new branch for your changes. Use a descriptive name for your branch to indicate the feature or fix you are working on:
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name

Make Changes: Implement your changes in the new branch. Ensure your code follows the project’s coding standards and is well-documented. All contributions must strictly adhere to Liber Creative LLC’s coding rules, as specified in each developer’s contract.
Commit Changes: Commit your changes with a clear and descriptive commit message:
git commit -m "Add feature: your-feature-name"

Push Changes: Push your changes to your fork on GitHub:
git push origin feature/your-feature-name

Open a Pull Request: Open a pull request from your branch to the main repository’s main branch. Provide a clear description of your changes, including:
The purpose of the changes.
Any relevant issue numbers (e.g., “Closes #123”).
A summary of the changes made.
Any additional information that may be helpful for the review.
Code Style
Please follow the existing code style and conventions used in the project. Ensure your code is well-documented and includes comments where necessary. All contributions must strictly adhere to Liber Creative LLC’s coding rules, as specified in each developer’s contract. 
We recommend using a linter to check your code for style issues before submitting a pull request.

License
By contributing to PI Creation Tool and any dependency, made by Liber Creative LLC and assigned as BSD 3-Clause Licensed, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the BSD 3-Clause License.
In any other cases it's Apache License 2.0 or equivalent.

Contact
If you have any questions or need further assistance, feel free to reach out to us through the GitHub repository or contact Nikita Beregovykh at nv@beregovykh.ru.

Thank you for your contributions!

Note: PI Creation Tool consists of more than 30.0% original code, with the remaining parts being standard Android framework and basic constructions. 
Keep your code clean and original, we are making future. Ask me directly, if you have any questions, no one's else responses may be legit at the moment.
